{
  "name": "ai-ses - CRM Sync",
  "nodes": [
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## ai-ses - CRM Sync\nProject-owned CRM delivery workflow for backend-owned lead and call outcome events.\n\nExpected inbound body shape:\n- kind: crm_webhook\n- office\n- entity\n- event\n- connection.config\n\nExpected trusted connection.config fields:\n- deliveryUrl\n\nDo not trust callback routing from request payload.\nBackend callback target stays fixed to the backend-owned CRM delivery callback contract.",
        "height": 360,
        "width": 500,
        "color": 5
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -920,
        -220
      ],
      "id": "6c4962d5-f8bb-4c9d-9604-bf7b7fddce90",
      "name": "Workflow Contract"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## Runtime Notes\n- Build with the Webhook node test URL first, then activate and switch to the production URL.\n- Inbound auth requires header x-ai-ses-trigger-secret to match {{$env.N8N_CRM_TRIGGER_SECRET}} before any outbound step runs.\n- CRM delivery target is read only from backend-authenticated office connection config: body.connection.config.deliveryUrl.\n- Backend callback always goes to {{$env.AI_SES_BACKEND_BASE_URL}}/v1/webhooks/n8n/crm-deliveries with fixed header x-ai-ses-callback-secret.\n- Backend callback writeback is best-effort. If it fails after CRM delivery work, the workflow still responds with callbackAccepted=false.\n- This workflow orchestrates delivery only. Backend remains the source of truth for office, entity, and lead qualification state.",
        "height": 340,
        "width": 460,
        "color": 6
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -920,
        220
      ],
      "id": "9afc0675-38f2-4a63-a14a-0312d06c5cd7",
      "name": "Runtime Notes"
    },
